Aminopeptidase N (APN, EC 3.4.11.2) is a zinc-dependent membrane type II endopeptidase. It belongs to the M1 family of MA clan (metallo-peptidase superfamily) of peptidases. It contains 967 amino acids and has a relative molecular mass (M\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
