The create recursive partitioning model protocol in DS was used to build the classification model. RP tree consists of internal nodes and leafs where each internal node corresponds to a test on one descriptor, and each leaf is assigned a classification label. The model was built by minimizing the Gini index [31] to divide these compounds into branches. Detailed protocol of RP is provided in supporting information (Text S2).

2D descriptors including function class fingerprints of maximum diameter 6 (FCFP_6), AlogP, MW, nRB, nR, nArR, nHBD, nHBA, and MFPSA were used for the Bayesian model generation using the Create Bayesian model protocol in DS. The model predictability was tested on the test set compounds.

